const e=JSON.parse('[{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","type":"title"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"saddle-world-tilemap","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"Chunk-based square, isometric, and hex tilemap foundation for Bevy. The crate keeps logical tile storage separate from render chunks and collision output. It is meant to stay generic enough for authored levels, procedural maps, runtime edits, multiple layers, and large scrolling worlds without tying the API to a specific editor or physics backend."},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Why this crate exists","anchor":"#why-this-crate-exists","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Why this crate exists","anchor":"#why-this-crate-exists","type":"content","content":"saddle-world-tilemap is meant to cover the durable shared-crate layer for: - authored 2D levels - procedural world generation - runtime tile edits and patching - multi-layer maps with logic-only collision layers - square, isometric, and hex coordinate conversion - autotiled terrain or road networks - animated tiles driven by shared tile definitions - Tiled JSON import with object-layer extraction The implementation studies ideas from Bevy\'s built-in tilemap chunk examples, bevyecstilemap, Tiled infinite maps, and LDtk auto-layers, but owns the runtime model directly."},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Quick start","anchor":"#quick-start","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Public API","anchor":"#public-api","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Plugin and scheduling","anchor":"#plugin-and-scheduling","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Plugin and scheduling","anchor":"#plugin-and-scheduling","type":"content","content":"- TilemapPlugin - TilemapSystems::{Prepare, ApplyCommands, AdvanceAnimation, ResolveAutotiling, SyncCollision, SyncRender, Debug} - injectable schedules through TilemapPlugin::new(...) - convenience constructors: TilemapPlugin::always_on(Update) and Default"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Runtime-facing components and messages","anchor":"#runtime-facing-components-and-messages","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Runtime-facing components and messages","anchor":"#runtime-facing-components-and-messages","type":"content","content":"- TilemapBundle - TilemapRoot - TilemapLayerNode - TilemapRenderChunk - TilemapCollisionChunk - TilemapDiagnostics - TilemapCommand - SetTile - ClearTile - FillRect - FillCircle - FillLine - FloodFill - SwapTiles - SetLayerVisibility - TileChanged - ChunkRebuilt - LayerVisibilityChanged - TileAnimationLooped"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate and geometry helpers","anchor":"#coordinate-and-geometry-helpers","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate and geometry helpers","anchor":"#coordinate-and-geometry-helpers","type":"content","content":"- TileCoord - ChunkCoord - TileRect - TilemapGeometry - TilemapOrientation::{Square, IsometricDiamond, HexPointyColumns, HexFlatRows} - TilemapHexParity - TileRowDirection TilemapGeometry exposes the main conversion helpers: - tiletolocal - localtotile - tiletoworld - worldtotile - cursortotile - chunkboundslocal"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Tile and layer model","anchor":"#tile-and-layer-model","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Tile and layer model","anchor":"#tile-and-layer-model","type":"content","content":"- Tilemap - TileChunk - TileLayerState - TileLayerConfig - TileLayerRenderConfig - TileCatalog - TileKind - TileKindId - TileCell - TileOrientation - TileAtlasLayout"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Autotiling, animation, and collision metadata","anchor":"#autotiling-animation-and-collision-metadata","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Autotiling, animation, and collision metadata","anchor":"#autotiling-animation-and-collision-metadata","type":"content","content":"- AutotileBinding - AutotileGroupId - AutotileRuleSetId - AutotileNeighborhood - AutotileRuleSet - computeautotilemask - TileAnimation - TileAnimationFrame - TileCollisionDescriptor - TileCollisionShape - TileCollisionCell"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Pathfinding","anchor":"#pathfinding","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Pathfinding","anchor":"#pathfinding","type":"content","content":"- findpath(map, layerid, start, goal, options) -> Option<TilePathResult> — A search on a tile layer, respecting movement costs and collision - findpathwithpolicy(map, layerid, start, goal, options, policy) -> Option<TilePathResult> — A with injectable passability and cost policy - reachabletiles(map, layerid, start, maxcost, diagonal) -> BTreeMap<TileCoord, u32> — Dijkstra flood returning all tiles reachable within a cost budget - reachabletileswithpolicy(map, layerid, start, maxcost, diagonal, policy) -> BTreeMap<TileCoord, u32> — Dijkstra flood with injectable passability and cost policy - TilePathOptions — configuration: maxcost, diagonal - TilePathResult — result: path: Vec<TileCoord>, totalcost: u32 - TilePathPolicy — trait hook for custom traversal rules - TilePathStep — per-edge query context passed into custom policies - TilePathCallbacks::new(passability, movementcost) — convenience adapter from closures - TileKindPathPolicy — built-in policy used by findpath and reachabletiles Pathfinding supports all orientation modes (square, isometric, hex). findpath and reachabletiles keep the existing built-in behavior through TileKindPathPolicy: the destination tile must exist on the queried layer, same-layer TileCollisionDescriptor blocks traversal, and TileKind.movementcost supplies the per-step cost. Use withpolicy when locomotion depends on different rules, such as: - reading a separate collision layer - preferring roads from a detail layer - agent-specific movement rules - directional or contextual terrain costs"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Fill helpers","anchor":"#fill-helpers","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Fill helpers","anchor":"#fill-helpers","type":"content","content":"Direct methods on Tilemap: - fillcircle(layerid, center, radius, tile) — Euclidean radius fill - fillline(layerid, from, to, tile) — Bresenham line rasterization - floodfill(layerid, start, tile, max_tiles) -> usize — flood fill with safety limit These are also available as TilemapCommand variants (FillCircle, FillLine, FloodFill) for message-driven usage."},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate helpers on `TileCoord`","anchor":"#coordinate-helpers-on-tilecoord","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate helpers on `TileCoord`","anchor":"#coordinate-helpers-on-tilecoord","type":"content","content":"- cardinalneighbors() — 4 orthogonal neighbors - eightneighbors() — 8 including diagonals - hexneighborspointy(parity) — 6 hex neighbors (pointy-top stagger) - hexneighborsflat(parity) — 6 hex neighbors (flat-top stagger) - manhattandistance(other) — L1 distance - chebyshevdistance(other) — L∞ distance"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Tiled import","anchor":"#tiled-import","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Tiled import","anchor":"#tiled-import","type":"content","content":"- importtiledjson_str - TiledImportOptions - ImportedTilemapScene - TileObjectSpawn - TilePropertyValue - TiledImportError"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate systems","anchor":"#coordinate-systems","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Coordinate systems","anchor":"#coordinate-systems","type":"content","content":"Shipped in 0.1.0: - square grids - isometric diamond grids - pointy-top hex grids stored as staggered columns - flat-top hex grids stored as staggered rows Deferred on purpose: - sparse storage backends - streaming activation windows - LDtk parsing - direct scene/entity spawning from editor data All geometry modes share the same logical map model. Only coordinate conversion, chunk mesh projection, and depth ordering change."},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Runtime model","anchor":"#runtime-model","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Runtime model","anchor":"#runtime-model","type":"content","content":"The important separation is: - Tilemap and TileLayerState own the logical tiles - render chunks are generated projections of the logical state - collision chunks are generated descriptors, not physics objects - autotile resolution and animation happen against tile definitions, not ad-hoc entities Tile edits mark dirty chunks. The runtime then resolves only the affected chunks and rebuilds only the render and collision surfaces that changed. TilemapDiagnostics::dirty_chunks reports distinct dirty chunk coordinates across resolve, render, and collision phases instead of double-counting the same chunk in multiple queues. When render asset resources are absent, the logical, animation, autotile, collision, and pathfinding phases still run. Render chunk sync is skipped automatically so the same plugin can stay active in logic-only tools, headless sims, or server-side validation passes."},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Examples","anchor":"#examples","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Examples","anchor":"#examples","type":"content","content":"Every shipped example now includes a live saddle-pane control surface for debug toggles and the most useful layout parameters. Run them with: Smoke-check the integration showcase with: Targeted interaction checks for the currently scripted examples:"},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Dependency philosophy","anchor":"#dependency-philosophy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"saddle-world-tilemap","slug":"/","heading":"Dependency philosophy","anchor":"#dependency-philosophy","type":"content","content":"Runtime dependency surface stays minimal: - bevy = \\"0.18\\" - serde - serdejson The crate still does not depend on gamecore, Avian, LDtk, or bevyecstilemap. Physics integration and editor-specific entity spawning stay adapter concerns outside the runtime crate, while Tiled JSON translation is now supported directly through a normalized import API."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","type":"title"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Design goals","anchor":"#design-goals","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Design goals","anchor":"#design-goals","type":"content","content":"saddle-world-tilemap is built around four rules: 1. logical tile storage is the source of truth 2. render chunks and collision chunks are projections of that logical state 3. runtime edits stay localized through dirty-chunk tracking 4. coordinate conversion remains explicit and testable"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Main runtime split","anchor":"#main-runtime-split","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Logical model","anchor":"#logical-model","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Logical model","anchor":"#logical-model","type":"content","content":"The public logical model is: - Tilemap - TileLayerState - TileChunk - TileCatalog - TileKind - TileCell Tilemap owns: - map geometry - chunk size - stable layer IDs - the per-layer chunk store TileLayerState owns: - the layer config - the catalog for that layer - dense chunk-local tile storage - dirty sets for resolve, render, and collision The logical model never stores render entities directly."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Runtime projection state","anchor":"#runtime-projection-state","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Runtime projection state","anchor":"#runtime-projection-state","type":"content","content":"Internal runtime state lives in TilemapRuntimeComponent and tracks: - spawned layer nodes - spawned render chunk entities - spawned collision chunk entities - animation playback state per animated tile kind This runtime cache is rebuildable. Deactivation clears it and leaves the logical tile state intact."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"System pipeline","anchor":"#system-pipeline","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"System pipeline","anchor":"#system-pipeline","type":"content","content":"TilemapSystems describes the intended frame order: 1. Prepare 2. ApplyCommands 3. AdvanceAnimation 4. ResolveAutotiling 5. SyncCollision 6. SyncRender 7. Debug"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`Prepare`","anchor":"#prepare","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`Prepare`","anchor":"#prepare","type":"content","content":"- ensures every map root has runtime state - spawns layer nodes lazily - initializes diagnostics - marks the full map dirty on first activation"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`ApplyCommands`","anchor":"#applycommands","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`ApplyCommands`","anchor":"#applycommands","type":"content","content":"- consumes TilemapCommand - mutates logical tiles only - emits TileChanged and LayerVisibilityChanged - marks the edited chunk, and neighboring chunks when autotile groups are involved"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`AdvanceAnimation`","anchor":"#advanceanimation","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`AdvanceAnimation`","anchor":"#advanceanimation","type":"content","content":"- advances per-kind animation clocks - marks only chunks containing the animated kind dirty when the visible frame changes - emits TileAnimationLooped when a clip wraps Animation is definition-driven. The system never creates one timer per tile entity."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`ResolveAutotiling`","anchor":"#resolveautotiling","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`ResolveAutotiling`","anchor":"#resolveautotiling","type":"content","content":"- walks dirty logical chunks - resolves each tile into: - final atlas index - tint/orientation - collision descriptor - animated-kind membership - increments the chunk revision - forwards the chunk to render and collision sync stages Autotiling uses reusable rule sets keyed by AutotileRuleSetId. The core implementation currently ships bitmask-style matching for cardinal or Moore neighborhoods."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`SyncCollision`","anchor":"#synccollision","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`SyncCollision`","anchor":"#synccollision","type":"content","content":"- rebuilds TilemapCollisionChunk components from resolved descriptors - despawns empty collision chunks - keeps collision output generic and backend-agnostic The crate deliberately stops at descriptors. A physics integration layer can translate them into colliders later."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`SyncRender`","anchor":"#syncrender","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`SyncRender`","anchor":"#syncrender","type":"content","content":"- rebuilds one mesh per dirty chunk per visual layer - keeps layer ordering and visibility on the layer node - uses chunk-local mesh projection based on TilemapGeometry - skips itself automatically when the app has no mesh/material asset resources, so logic-only or headless integrations can keep the rest of the runtime active The current backend is a simple internal chunk mesh builder using Mesh2d and ColorMaterial. The public crate surface does not expose the renderer internals so this can evolve later."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`Debug`","anchor":"#debug","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"`Debug`","anchor":"#debug","type":"content","content":"- draws chunk bounds and dirty chunks through gizmos when GizmoPlugin is present - stays optional and data-driven through TilemapDebugSettings and TilemapDebugOverlay"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Chunk lifecycle","anchor":"#chunk-lifecycle","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Chunk lifecycle","anchor":"#chunk-lifecycle","type":"content","content":"1. logical edits create or mutate TileChunk 2. the layer marks the chunk dirty 3. resolution computes final visual and collision snapshots 4. sync stages spawn or update chunk entities 5. empty chunks despawn their render and collision projections Chunk coordinates are stable through ChunkCoord. Tile-to-chunk math uses Euclidean division so negative coordinates remain coherent."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Coordinate architecture","anchor":"#coordinate-architecture","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Coordinate architecture","anchor":"#coordinate-architecture","type":"content","content":"TilemapGeometry is the only place that knows how a logical tile maps into local or world space. Current modes: - Square - IsometricDiamond - HexPointyColumns - HexFlatRows The same public helpers are used for: - tile placement - cursor picking - world-to-tile conversion - chunk debug rectangles This keeps authored content, procedural generation, and runtime picking on the same math path."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Pathfinding","anchor":"#pathfinding","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Pathfinding","anchor":"#pathfinding","type":"content","content":"The crate includes two standalone pathfinding functions that operate directly on the logical tile model: - findpath — A search on a named tile layer, returning the optimal path as a Vec<TileCoord> with total accumulated cost - reachabletiles — Dijkstra flood from a starting tile, returning all tiles reachable within a cost budget Both are convenience wrappers over: - findpathwithpolicy - reachabletileswithpolicy - TilePathPolicy - TilePathStep - TilePathCallbacks Both functions: - read tile data from TileLayerState without spawning entities - require the destination tile to exist on the queried layer under the built-in policy - default to TileKindPathPolicy, which treats same-layer TileCollisionDescriptor tiles as impassable - default to TileKind.movementcost as the per-tile cost - support all orientation modes through tile_neighbors(), which dispatches to cardinal, 8-directional, or hex-6 neighborhoods based on TilemapOrientation Custom policies receive a TilePathStep containing the current map, the queried layer, source and destination coordinates, and the resolved source/destination tile metadata for that layer. This allows callers to implement richer locomotion models, such as consulting a separate collision layer, detail-layer roads, or agent-specific movement rules, without changing the logical tile storage."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Design choice","anchor":"#design-choice","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Design choice","anchor":"#design-choice","type":"content","content":"Pathfinding operates on the logical model, not on render or collision projections. This means it stays usable even when rendering is disabled or collision chunks have not been synced yet."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Fill helpers","anchor":"#fill-helpers","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"Fill helpers","anchor":"#fill-helpers","type":"content","content":"The Tilemap struct provides three fill methods for common editing operations: - fillcircle — fills all tiles within a Euclidean radius - fillline — Bresenham line rasterization between two tile coordinates - flood_fill — BFS flood fill from a starting tile, replacing matching tiles up to a configurable safety limit These are also exposed as TilemapCommand variants (FillCircle, FillLine, FloodFill) for message-driven usage through MessageWriter<TilemapCommand>."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"What is intentionally not in the core runtime","anchor":"#what-is-intentionally-not-in-the-core-runtime","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Architecture","slug":"/docs/architecture/","heading":"What is intentionally not in the core runtime","anchor":"#what-is-intentionally-not-in-the-core-runtime","type":"content","content":"- sparse storage - streaming activation or chunk culling - physics backend bindings - navmesh or visibility baking - save/load formats Tiled JSON translation now ships directly in the crate as a normalized import boundary. LDtk parsing and editor-specific scene/entity instantiation still stay outside the core runtime. Those are useful adapter layers, but they are not part of the durable core runtime contract in 0.1.0."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","type":"title"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapPlugin`","anchor":"#tilemapplugin","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapPlugin`","anchor":"#tilemapplugin","type":"content","content":"Runtime integration surface for logical maps, chunk sync, animation, and debug drawing."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields","type":"content","content":"- activateschedule: Interned<dyn ScheduleLabel> - deactivateschedule: Interned<dyn ScheduleLabel> - updateschedule: Interned<dyn ScheduleLabel> - debugsettings: TilemapDebugSettings"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors","type":"content","content":"- TilemapPlugin::new(activate, deactivate, update) - TilemapPlugin::alwayson(update) - TilemapPlugin::default() which is equivalent to alwayson(Update) - withdebugsettings(TilemapDebugSettings)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance","type":"content","content":"- use new(...) for state-scoped gameplay or tool modes - use always_on(Update) for examples, editors, or always-live world tooling - if GizmoPlugin is not present, the debug draw system is skipped automatically - if render asset resources are not available, render chunk sync is skipped automatically and the logical/collision runtime still works"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapGeometry`","anchor":"#tilemapgeometry","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapGeometry`","anchor":"#tilemapgeometry","type":"content","content":"Controls tile placement, world conversion, and chunk bounds."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-1","type":"content","content":"- orientation: TilemapOrientation - gridsize: Vec2 - tilerendersize: Vec2 - origin: Vec2 - rowdirection: TileRowDirection"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-1","type":"content","content":"- TilemapGeometry::square(tilesize) - TilemapGeometry::isometricdiamond(tilerendersize) - TilemapGeometry::hexpointycolumns(tilerendersize, TilemapHexParity) - TilemapGeometry::hexflatrows(tilerendersize, TilemapHexParity)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Orientation variants","anchor":"#orientation-variants","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Orientation variants","anchor":"#orientation-variants","type":"content","content":"- TilemapOrientation::Square - TilemapOrientation::IsometricDiamond - TilemapOrientation::HexPointyColumns(TilemapHexParity) - TilemapOrientation::HexFlatRows(TilemapHexParity)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapHexParity`","anchor":"#tilemaphexparity","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapHexParity`","anchor":"#tilemaphexparity","type":"content","content":"- TilemapHexParity::Odd - TilemapHexParity::Even"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders","type":"content","content":"- withorigin(Vec2) - withrowdirection(TileRowDirection) - withtilerendersize(Vec2)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-1","type":"content","content":"- keep gridsize.x > 0.0 and gridsize.y > 0.0 - for square maps, gridsize and tilerendersize usually match - for isometric maps, gridsize should stay half-width and half-height of the rendered diamond unless you are intentionally stretching or overlapping tiles - for pointy-column hex maps, tilerendersize should match the full rendered hex footprint and parity should match the source data layout - for flat-row hex maps, tilerendersize should match the full rendered hex footprint and parity should match the source data layout - row_direction = Down matches common 2D screen-space conventions"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`Tilemap`","anchor":"#tilemap","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`Tilemap`","anchor":"#tilemap","type":"content","content":"Top-level logical map component."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-2","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-2","type":"content","content":"- geometry: TilemapGeometry - chunk_size: UVec2 - layers: BTreeMap<TileLayerId, TileLayerState>"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-2","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-2","type":"content","content":"- chunk sizes between 8x8 and 32x32 are the practical starting range - smaller chunks reduce the cost of isolated edits - larger chunks reduce entity and mesh counts for mostly static maps"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileLayerConfig`","anchor":"#tilelayerconfig","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileLayerConfig`","anchor":"#tilelayerconfig","type":"content","content":"Per-layer authored configuration."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-3","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-3","type":"content","content":"- id: TileLayerId - name: String - visible: bool - offset: Vec2 - render: Option<TileLayerRenderConfig>"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-2","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-2","type":"content","content":"- TileLayerConfig::visual(id, name, render) - TileLayerConfig::logiconly(id, name) - withoffset(Vec2)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-3","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-3","type":"content","content":"- use logic_only(...) for collision, navigation, or metadata layers that should not render - prefer stable TileLayerId values for persistence or editor adapters - use offset sparingly; it is best for parallax or overlay alignment, not as a replacement for a coherent map transform"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileLayerRenderConfig`","anchor":"#tilelayerrenderconfig","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileLayerRenderConfig`","anchor":"#tilelayerrenderconfig","type":"content","content":"Visual settings for a renderable layer."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-4","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-4","type":"content","content":"- atlas: TileAtlasLayout - zindex: f32 - tint: Color - alphamode: AlphaMode2d - chunksortstep: f32"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Defaults","anchor":"#defaults","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Defaults","anchor":"#defaults","type":"content","content":"- zindex = 0.0 - tint = Color::WHITE - alphamode = AlphaMode2d::Blend - chunksortstep = 0.0001"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-1","type":"content","content":"- withzindex(f32) - withtint(Color) - withalphamode(AlphaMode2d) - withchunksortstep(f32)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-4","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-4","type":"content","content":"- use larger zindex values for overlays, highlights, or decals - chunksort_step matters for isometric and hex chunk ordering - transparent oversized art should live on a dedicated layer when you need explicit ordering control"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileAtlasLayout`","anchor":"#tileatlaslayout","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileAtlasLayout`","anchor":"#tileatlaslayout","type":"content","content":"Describes how atlas indices map into UVs."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-5","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-5","type":"content","content":"- image: Handle<Image> - texturesize: UVec2 - tilesize: UVec2 - columns: u32 - rows: u32 - padding: UVec2 - margin: UVec2"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors and builders","anchor":"#constructors-and-builders","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors and builders","anchor":"#constructors-and-builders","type":"content","content":"- TileAtlasLayout::fromgrid(image, texturesize, tilesize, columns, rows) - withpadding(UVec2) - with_margin(UVec2)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-5","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-5","type":"content","content":"- columns * rows defines the valid atlas index range - set padding and margin when importing atlas sheets that were packed with gutters - prefer nearest sampling in examples or pixel-art workflows"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileKind`","anchor":"#tilekind","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileKind`","anchor":"#tilekind","type":"content","content":"Reusable tile definition."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-6","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-6","type":"content","content":"- name: String - render: TileRenderRule - collision: Option<TileCollisionDescriptor> - flags: u32 - movement_cost: u16"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-3","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructors","anchor":"#constructors-3","type":"content","content":"- TileKind::statictile(name, atlasindex) - TileKind::animated_tile(name, TileAnimation) - TileKind::autotile(name, AutotileBinding)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-2","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-2","type":"content","content":"- withcollision(TileCollisionDescriptor) - withflags(u32) - withmovementcost(u16)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-6","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-6","type":"content","content":"- keep tile definitions reusable and data-oriented - use flags for small shared bitfields, not game-specific object graphs - movement_cost = 1 is the intended baseline"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`AutotileRuleSet`","anchor":"#autotileruleset","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`AutotileRuleSet`","anchor":"#autotileruleset","type":"content","content":"Rule table for reusable autotile matching."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-7","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-7","type":"content","content":"- neighborhood: AutotileNeighborhood - variants: BTreeMap<u16, u32> - fallbackatlasindex: u32"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-7","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-7","type":"content","content":"- Cardinal4 fits roads, rivers, walls, and pipe-style connectors - Moore8 is more appropriate for full blob or terrain masks - missing masks fall back to fallbackatlasindex"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileAnimation`","anchor":"#tileanimation","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileAnimation`","anchor":"#tileanimation","type":"content","content":"Definition-driven animated tile clip."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-8","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-8","type":"content","content":"- frames: Vec<TileAnimationFrame>"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-8","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-8","type":"content","content":"- frame durations should stay positive - animation cost scales with the number of chunks containing the animated kind, not the number of tile entities"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapDebugSettings`","anchor":"#tilemapdebugsettings","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilemapDebugSettings`","anchor":"#tilemapdebugsettings","type":"content","content":"Runtime debug resource."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-9","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-9","type":"content","content":"- enabled: bool - drawchunkbounds: bool - drawdirtychunks: bool - chunkcolor: Color - dirtycolor: Color - collision_color: Color"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Defaults","anchor":"#defaults-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Defaults","anchor":"#defaults-1","type":"content","content":"- enabled = false - chunk bounds enabled - dirty chunk bounds enabled"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-9","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-9","type":"content","content":"- enable this in labs and sandboxes, not by default in shipping game scenes - dirty chunk drawing is useful for validating edit locality and animation rebuild scopes"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathOptions`","anchor":"#tilepathoptions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathOptions`","anchor":"#tilepathoptions","type":"content","content":"Options for the A* pathfinding algorithm."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-10","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-10","type":"content","content":"- max_cost: u32 — maximum total path cost before giving up. Default: u32::MAX - diagonal: bool — whether to allow diagonal movement on square/iso grids. Default: false"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-3","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Builders","anchor":"#builders-3","type":"content","content":"- withmaxcost(u32) - with_diagonal(bool)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-10","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-10","type":"content","content":"- set max_cost to limit search radius for performance or gameplay reasons - diagonal = true allows 8-directional movement; path steps include diagonals - hex grids ignore the diagonal flag and always use 6 neighbors"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathResult`","anchor":"#tilepathresult","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathResult`","anchor":"#tilepathresult","type":"content","content":"Result of a successful pathfinding query."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-11","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-11","type":"content","content":"- path: Vec<TileCoord> — ordered tile coordinates from start to goal (inclusive) - total_cost: u32 — accumulated movement cost along the path"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileKindPathPolicy`","anchor":"#tilekindpathpolicy","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TileKindPathPolicy`","anchor":"#tilekindpathpolicy","type":"content","content":"Built-in pathfinding policy used by findpath(...) and reachabletiles(...)."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Behavior","anchor":"#behavior","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Behavior","anchor":"#behavior","type":"content","content":"- destination tiles must exist on the queried layer - same-layer tiles with TileCollisionDescriptor are impassable - same-layer TileKind.movement_cost is used as the per-step cost"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-11","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-11","type":"content","content":"- use this when the queried layer already contains the locomotion metadata you want - switch to findpathwithpolicy(...) or reachabletileswithpolicy(...) when movement depends on other layers or agent-specific rules"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathStep<\'a>`","anchor":"#tilepathstep-a","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathStep<\'a>`","anchor":"#tilepathstep-a","type":"content","content":"Context passed into custom TilePathPolicy implementations and TilePathCallbacks."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-12","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-12","type":"content","content":"- map: &Tilemap - layerid: TileLayerId - layer: &TileLayerState - from: TileCoord - to: TileCoord - fromtile: Option<&TileCell> - fromkind: Option<&TileKind> - totile: Option<&TileCell> - to_kind: Option<&TileKind>"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-12","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-12","type":"content","content":"- inspect tokind / totile for same-layer terrain decisions - inspect map when passability or cost depends on other layers - prefer positive movement costs for passable tiles"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathCallbacks`","anchor":"#tilepathcallbacks","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TilePathCallbacks`","anchor":"#tilepathcallbacks","type":"content","content":"Closure adapter for custom pathfinding rules."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructor","anchor":"#constructor","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructor","anchor":"#constructor","type":"content","content":"- TilePathCallbacks::new(passability, movement_cost)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-13","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-13","type":"content","content":"- use this for one-off closures in examples, tools, or gameplay systems - implement TilePathPolicy directly for reusable agent types or locomotion presets"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TiledImportOptions`","anchor":"#tiledimportoptions","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`TiledImportOptions`","anchor":"#tiledimportoptions","type":"content","content":"Runtime import surface for normalized Tiled JSON ingestion."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-13","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-13","type":"content","content":"- atlas: TileAtlasLayout - catalog: TileCatalog - gidtokind: BTreeMap<u32, TileKindId> - chunksize: UVec2 - origin: Vec2 - rowdirection: TileRowDirection - layerzstep: f32 - logiconlylayers: BTreeSet<String>"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructor","anchor":"#constructor-1","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Constructor","anchor":"#constructor-1","type":"content","content":"- TiledImportOptions::new(atlas, catalog, gidtokind)"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-14","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Guidance","anchor":"#guidance-14","type":"content","content":"- gidtokind should map stripped Tiled global tile IDs, not flip-flagged values - logiconlylayers is useful for collision, nav, and metadata layers that should import but not render - layerzstep becomes the per-layer zindex increment for imported visual layers - origin and rowdirection should match the world-space convention used by the rest of your app"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"`ImportedTilemapScene`","anchor":"#importedtilemapscene","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-14","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Configuration","slug":"/docs/configuration/","heading":"Fields","anchor":"#fields-14","type":"content","content":"- map: Tilemap - object_spawns: Vec<TileObjectSpawn> The importer intentionally returns normalized object-layer spawn descriptors instead of spawning entities directly. That keeps scene/entity instantiation policy outside the durable tile runtime."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","type":"title"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","anchor":"","type":"content","content":"saddle-world-tilemap now ships a normalized Tiled JSON importer and still keeps LDtk as an adapter concern. The core data model remains the durable runtime boundary either way."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Integration rule","anchor":"#integration-rule","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Integration rule","anchor":"#integration-rule","type":"content","content":"Treat editor data as an import boundary, not as the runtime model. The adapter\'s job is to translate editor concepts into: - Tilemap - TileLayerState - TileCatalog - TileKind - TileCell - TileLayerId - TileCollisionDescriptor Once that translation is done, gameplay code should only talk to the saddle-world-tilemap runtime types."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Built-in Tiled path","anchor":"#built-in-tiled-path","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Built-in Tiled path","anchor":"#built-in-tiled-path","type":"content","content":"Use importtiledjson_str(...) when you want to translate a Tiled JSON asset directly into: - Tilemap - TileLayerState - TileObjectSpawn The caller still owns: - tileset asset loading - gid -> TileKindId mapping - which imported layers are visual vs logic-only - how object-layer spawns become actual entities or scenes"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Mapping Tiled concepts","anchor":"#mapping-tiled-concepts","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Infinite maps","anchor":"#infinite-maps","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Infinite maps","anchor":"#infinite-maps","type":"content","content":"Tiled infinite maps already think in chunks. A Tiled adapter can map each incoming chunk to: - ChunkCoord - dense tile data inside TileChunk The runtime crate does not need to know whether a chunk came from Tiled, procedural generation, or a save file."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Global tile IDs","anchor":"#global-tile-ids","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Global tile IDs","anchor":"#global-tile-ids","type":"content","content":"Tiled GIDs should be resolved by the adapter into: - a TileKindId - optional TileOrientation derived from flip flags The adapter should strip flip bits and own any tileset lookup tables. The runtime crate should only receive normalized tile IDs and orientations."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Tile properties","anchor":"#tile-properties","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Tile properties","anchor":"#tile-properties","type":"content","content":"Tiled custom properties can map into: - flags - movement_cost - TileCollisionDescriptor - adapter-owned side tables if the data is too editor-specific for the shared crate Avoid pushing arbitrary editor schemas into the core runtime."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Layer ordering","anchor":"#layer-ordering","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Layer ordering","anchor":"#layer-ordering","type":"content","content":"Tiled layer order should become stable TileLayerId values plus zindex values in TileLayerRenderConfig. Use logiconly(...) for collision or metadata layers that should not render."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Mapping LDtk concepts","anchor":"#mapping-ldtk-concepts","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Auto-layers","anchor":"#auto-layers","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Auto-layers","anchor":"#auto-layers","type":"content","content":"LDtk auto-layers are a good mental model for AutotileRuleSet, but the runtime crate does not execute LDtk rules directly. An LDtk adapter should translate: - terrain or auto-layer output into final TileCell values - reusable auto-layer semantics into AutotileBinding and AutotileRuleSet where that preserves value"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"IntGrid and metadata layers","anchor":"#intgrid-and-metadata-layers","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"IntGrid and metadata layers","anchor":"#intgrid-and-metadata-layers","type":"content","content":"LDtk IntGrid layers are a good fit for: - flags - movement or traversal cost side tables - logic-only layers If the data is more expressive than a u32 flag set, keep the richer structure in an adapter-owned asset and use saddle-world-tilemap only for the cross-cutting runtime pieces."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Recommended workflow","anchor":"#recommended-workflow","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"Recommended workflow","anchor":"#recommended-workflow","type":"content","content":"1. Load or parse the external editor format into an adapter-owned asset. 2. Build a TileCatalog from the referenced tilesets. 3. Allocate stable TileLayerId values for each runtime layer. 4. Convert the editor coordinates into TileCoord. 5. Populate TileLayerState and Tilemap, or call importtiledjson_str(...) for Tiled JSON. 6. Spawn the result through TilemapBundle. This keeps editor concerns isolated from the runtime crate and makes it easier to support multiple import sources later."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"What should stay outside the core crate","anchor":"#what-should-stay-outside-the-core-crate","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Editor Integration","slug":"/docs/editor-integration/","heading":"What should stay outside the core crate","anchor":"#what-should-stay-outside-the-core-crate","type":"content","content":"- LDtk parsing - tileset asset resolution policies - entity or scene spawning policy - editor-specific property schemas - one-off content rules Those are adapter concerns. The shared crate should stay focused on durable tile runtime behavior."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","type":"title"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Current runtime model","anchor":"#current-runtime-model","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Current runtime model","anchor":"#current-runtime-model","type":"content","content":"The 0.1.0 runtime is dense and chunk-based: - each logical layer stores dense TileChunk buffers - each dirty visual chunk becomes one mesh entity - each dirty collision chunk becomes one descriptor entity This is a good fit for: - authored levels - procedural maps with predictable density - runtime edits localized to a few chunks - large scrolling maps that stay fully resident It is not yet a sparse or streamed backend."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Chunk size guidance","anchor":"#chunk-size-guidance","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Chunk size guidance","anchor":"#chunk-size-guidance","type":"content","content":"Chunk size is the main tuning knob."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Smaller chunks","anchor":"#smaller-chunks","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Smaller chunks","anchor":"#smaller-chunks","type":"content","content":"Good when: - single-tile edits are frequent - runtime brushes are local - animated tiles only affect small pockets of the world Tradeoffs: - more chunk entities - more mesh assets - more bookkeeping"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Larger chunks","anchor":"#larger-chunks","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Larger chunks","anchor":"#larger-chunks","type":"content","content":"Good when: - the world is mostly static - the map is dense - entity count matters more than isolated edit cost Tradeoffs: - one small edit rebuilds more geometry - chunk-local autotile and collision sync work touches more tiles"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Practical starting points","anchor":"#practical-starting-points","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Practical starting points","anchor":"#practical-starting-points","type":"content","content":"- 8x8 or 12x12: edit-heavy maps, builders, sandboxes - 16x16: balanced general-purpose default - 24x24 or 32x32: denser, more static worlds"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Runtime edit costs","anchor":"#runtime-edit-costs","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"`SetTile` and `ClearTile`","anchor":"#settile-and-cleartile","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"`SetTile` and `ClearTile`","anchor":"#settile-and-cleartile","type":"content","content":"The logical mutation is cheap. The cost comes from the follow-up projection work: 1. mark the owning chunk dirty 2. resolve the chunk 3. rebuild the visual mesh and collision descriptors for that chunk"},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Autotile edits","anchor":"#autotile-edits","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Autotile edits","anchor":"#autotile-edits","type":"content","content":"Autotile edits mark the edited chunk and any neighboring chunks that contain affected cells. This keeps the work local, but roads, rivers, and pipe networks near chunk seams will rebuild more than one chunk."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Batch edits","anchor":"#batch-edits","type":"heading","level":3},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Batch edits","anchor":"#batch-edits","type":"content","content":"Grouped edits to the same chunk are cheap relative to scattering one edit across many chunks. If you are applying a brush or procedural patch, prefer batching by chunk when possible."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Animated tile costs","anchor":"#animated-tile-costs","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Animated tile costs","anchor":"#animated-tile-costs","type":"content","content":"Animated tiles do not create one timer per tile. The runtime tracks playback per animated kind. When the visible frame changes: - only chunks containing that animated kind are marked dirty - only those chunks re-resolve and rebuild This keeps the cost proportional to affected chunks, not total tile count."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Large map behavior","anchor":"#large-map-behavior","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Large map behavior","anchor":"#large-map-behavior","type":"content","content":"The crate-local lab includes a dense 96x96 map as a practical smoke case. In the current implementation: - all chunks stay resident once built - camera motion does not stream chunks in or out - camera sweeps are mostly a renderer and transform test, not a streaming test If you need true streaming or sparse residency, that should be a later backend extension rather than a hidden side effect of the current API."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Dense vs sparse tradeoff","anchor":"#dense-vs-sparse-tradeoff","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Dense vs sparse tradeoff","anchor":"#dense-vs-sparse-tradeoff","type":"content","content":"The current crate is dense-only. Mostly-empty infinite worlds will waste memory compared with a sparse backend. This is an intentional 0.1.0 limit: - dense chunks keep access predictable and simple - runtime edits stay straightforward - editor import paths remain easy to reason about Sparse storage can be added later behind the same logical surface if it proves necessary."},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Debugging locality","anchor":"#debugging-locality","type":"heading","level":2},{"title":"`saddle-world-tilemap` Performance","slug":"/docs/performance/","heading":"Debugging locality","anchor":"#debugging-locality","type":"content","content":"Enable TilemapDebugSettings in labs or tools to validate: - chunk bounds - dirty chunk scopes - how many chunks each runtime edit touches - whether animation rebuilds stay localized TilemapDiagnostics is meant for the same workflow. It exposes enough counters for BRP and E2E tests to catch accidental broad rebuilds. dirty_chunks is reported as a distinct chunk count across resolve, render, and collision queues so one hot chunk does not look three times dirtier than it really is."}]');export{e as default};
